Power Spore

Amplifies the effects of all primary statuses on the field.

Details

This ability amplifies the effects of status conditions of all Pokémon on the field, including the wielder.

  • Paralysis: the chance that a paralyzed Pokémon is fully paralyzed on its turn increases from 25% to 30%.
  • Infatuation: the chance that an infatuated Pokémon fails to act on its turn increases from 50% to 60%.
  • Burn and Frostbite: damage from these status conditions is increased from 1/16th to 1/12th of the afflicted Pokémon's maximum HP.
  • Poison: damage from these status conditions is increased from 1/8th to 1/6th of the afflicted Pokémon's maximum HP.
  • Toxic poison: the initial damage due to toxic poison is 1/15th rather than 1/16th of the afflicted Pokémon's maximum HP, and the damage increases by 1/15th each turn rather than 1/16th.
  • Confusion: a confused Pokémon's chance of hurting itself increases from 33% to 60%.
  • Sleep: a Pokémon which falls asleep while Power Spore is active on the field will sleep from 2 to 4 turns instead of 1 to 3 turns. This does not affect Pokémon which fall asleep due to using the move Rest.
